{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_102","type":"agent_message","text":"Two remaining issues are now distinct: one real metadata miss (`SimpleFormatter` is conditioned too narrowly during startup logging), and one test that cannot behave the same way once Spring Boot runs fully in AOT mode (`NoSuchMethodFailureAnalyzerTest` needs its bean wired through the placeholder initializer). The ANSI test is a launcher mismatch rather than a metadata problem, so I’m checking whether the repo already has a native-only skip pattern before I decide between a targeted skip and a heavier child-process bootstrap."}}
